title: Box, mid- 18th century
creditline: Gift of C. Gustave Mourraille in memory of his sister, M. Mathilde Mourraille
description:
Rectangular box with hinged cover (sliding top?). The sides of copper. Top and bottom have cut-out figures feasting and quarreling respectively, framed in scroll work. 
b) sliding top, covering scene on bottom. Similar top for cover missing.

tombstone.epitaph:
Box, mid- 18th century.
mid- 18th century. Engraved brass and copper. Gift of C. Gustave Mourraille in memory of his sister, M. Mathilde Mourraille. 1957-121-8-a,b.
